#### The Association of Christians in the Mathematical Sciences was founded in 1977 as a network of Christian mathematicians dedicated to integrating  mathematics with faith and to promoting quality teaching.

News
----

ACMS / CES 25th Biennial Conference registration is open.
=========================================================

##### The Association of Christians in the Mathematical Sciences (ACMS) and the Christian Engineering Society (CES) joint conference will be held from May 27 – 30, 2026 at Calvin University, Grand Rapids, MI, USA. Conference registration is now open.

For full information about the conference, [click here](/2026-acms-conference-calvin/).

**Important Dates:**

**Register by March 31, 2026 to avoid late fees.
ACMS: Submit talk proposals by March 1, 2026.
CES: Submit talk proposals by November 1, 2025.** 

![](/media/ACMS-Poster-768x1024.png)

### **Dr. Karl-Dieter Crisman** has been selected as the ACMS Brabenec Lecturer for 2025-26.

Karl-Dieter Crisman is Professor of Mathematics and Computer Science at Gordon College, with degrees from Northwestern, Chicago, and Roosevelt.

Find out more about Karl-Dieter and the [Brabenec Lectureship](/brabenec-lectureship/) here.

**If your institution is interested in hosting Karl-Dieter this next academic year, [you can apply here](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdWpVc98gWoyaILiynnDrNFw-IEOTDEOFNfFWIbwLjD3v-GFw/viewform). The deadline to apply is August 22.**

